{"data":{"markdownRemark":null,"npmPackage":{"name":"gatsby-remark-graph","description":"Make nice graphs in your markdown files in gatsbyjs, using mermaid","keywords":["gatsby","gatsby-plugin","graph","mermaid","remark"],"lastPublisher":{"name":"konsumer","avatar":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/6695becc0d4f42e649921d5c69561cb4"},"repository":{"url":"https://github.com/konsumer/gatsby-remark-graph"},"readme":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"gatsby-remark-graph\"><a href=\"#gatsby-remark-graph\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>gatsby-remark-graph</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://greenkeeper.io/\"><img src=\"https://badges.greenkeeper.io/konsumer/gatsby-remark-graph.svg\" alt=\"Greenkeeper badge\"></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/konsumer/gatsby-remark-graph\"><img src=\"https://travis-ci.org/konsumer/gatsby-remark-graph.svg?branch=master\" alt=\"Travis Status\"></a></p>\n<p>Make nice graphs in your markdown files in gatsbyjs, using <a href=\"https://mermaidjs.github.io/\">mermaid</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://remark-graph-demo.netlify.com/graphdemo\">Here</a> is a basic demo, which also uses my <a href=\"https://github.com/konsumer/gatsby-starter-bootstrap-netlify/\">starter template</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"install\"><a href=\"#install\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>install</h2>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm install --save gatsby-transformer-remark gatsby-remark-graph</code></p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-use\"><a href=\"#how-to-use\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\">\n      <pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">// In your gatsby-config.js</span>\nplugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'gatsby-transformer-remark'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n          resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'gatsby-remark-graph'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n          options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"token comment\">// this is the language in your code-block that triggers mermaid parsing</span>\n            language<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'mermaid'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// default</span>\n            theme<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'default'</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// could also be dark, forest, or neutral</span>\n          <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Make sure you put it before other plugins (especially those that work with <code class=\"language-text\">code</code> blocks, like <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-remark-prismjs/\">prism</a>.)</p>\n<h3 id=\"usage-in-markdown\"><a href=\"#usage-in-markdown\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Usage in Markdown</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\">\n      <pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    A[Square Rect] -- Link text --&gt; B((Circle))\n    A --&gt; C(Round Rect)\n    B --&gt; D{Rhombus}\n    C --&gt; D\n```</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Will give you a graph that looks like this:</p>\n<p><img src=\"graph.png\" alt=\"diagram\"></p>","timeToRead":1}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/packages/gatsby-remark-graph/","id":"3a7cfda0-733e-5e4a-a7f8-d739d6eb3215"}}